          "date": "2012-10-05 10:25:44.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-07 18:31:09.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2089 ofd: do not pin pages provided by osd",
        "message": "LU-2089 ofd: do not pin pages provided by osd\n\ndepending on implementation, some pages can be allocated\nin order > 0 and kernel does increase refcounter on the\nfirst page only. in this case ptlrpc_free_bulk() calling\ncfs_unpin() will try to release such pages leading to\nwarning and other bad things in the kernel.\n\ninstead let ofd/ost to rely on dbo_bufs_get/dbo_bufs_put\nas they know details of the pages provided.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I3591e21eef9557d6004d29e63986c7bd5987802b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
